    "hash": "7uheo0Wdjwe7OJdlDZR8TO7nKho=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# mcp workflows\n\nWorkflows and sequencing rules for interacting with the reactor-mcp toolset.\n\n## Schema-First Rule\n- [[always check document model schema before calling addActions]] \u2014 prevents failed calls from missing required parameters\n\n## Batch Operations\n- [[batch multiple actions in a single addActions call to minimize round trips]] \u2014 combine related operations\n\n## Two-Step Modification\n- [[document model changes require both MCP update and src file update]] \u2014 never skip either step\n\n## Document Creation\n- [[document IDs are auto-generated by createDocument never set manually]] \u2014 let the system generate IDs\n- [[document models must be added to the vetra drive by default]] \u2014 source documents go to vetra drive\n- [[present document model proposals to user before implementing]] \u2014 planning phase is mandatory\n\n## App Creation\n- [[SET_APP_STATUS with CONFIRMED triggers code generation for apps]] \u2014 CONFIRMED status kicks off generation\n\n## Drive Operations\n- [[delete nodes with DELETE_NODE not DELETE_FILE]] \u2014 correct operation name for removing nodes\n- [[vetra drive holds source documents while preview drive holds instances]] \u2014 two drives, different purposes\n\n## Reducer Code via MCP\n- [[reducer code goes into SET_OPERATION_REDUCER without function headers]] \u2014 body only, no wrapper\n- [[external imports go in src reducer files not in SET_OPERATION_REDUCER]] \u2014 imports in src/ only\n\n## Prerequisites\n- [[reactor-mcp must be running before document operations]] \u2014 user must start with `ph vetra`\n\n## Reference\n- [[document models have 37 available operations across 7 categories]] \u2014 full operation taxonomy\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[index]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
